{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Create a premium ecommerce product slider exactly like a modern “Newly In” product rail. Requirements: Total products: 9 Visible at a time: 4 product cards Autoplay every 3 seconds Sliding behavior must be shift-by-one (not page-based): On each slide, the first visible product slides out The 5th product enters as the 4th card After the 9th product, the loop must feel seamless: 9th product shifts left (4th → 3rd → 2nd) 1st product re-enters from the right and becomes the last visible card Continuous, infinite loop with no jump or reset flash Card layout (must match exactly): Product image centered, fixed size, consistent ratio across all cards Top-left: rounded pill showing product tag / collection name Top-right: rating pill (e.g., 4.8 ★) Product name bold Pricing row aligned to match visual balance: Price on the left side of the card (primary focus) Compare-at price struck through (if present) Offer row below price: On the right side: black pill text “₹100 Extra Off” Next to it: green text “At Checkout” Visual style: Clean, premium, Apple/Boat-style UI Rounded cards, soft background Smooth horizontal animation (no snapping) Desktop-first layout, exact spacing and alignment Tech constraints: Shopify-compatible section No default carousel libraries CSS + JavaScript based infinite slider Performance-optimized and production-ready i wanna add some products which while im touching this means it will goes to the specific product
{% enddoc %}
{% assign ai_gen_id = block.id | replace: '_', '' | downcase %}

{% style %}
